Instruction: With the system assembled as currently configured and all control-module switches ON, measure the DC voltage between the Load Module’s (+) and (−) input terminals with a multimeter. Then, with power removed, continuity‑test from the Load Module (+) input terminal through the series diode to the lamp and lamp‑indicator junction, and from that junction back to the (−) input terminal, to verify that the diode and lamps form an intact series/parallel path and that the diode orientation is correct with respect to the identified (+) and (−) lines.
