ACTION:
With battery inserted and all switches ON, measure DC voltage on the positive and negative series lines at: (1) PSU output, (2) Control Module 1 input, (3) Control Module 1 output, (4) Control Module 2 input, and (5) Control Module 2 output, all with respect to the PSU negative. Then, with power removed, continuity‑test specifically the closed switch paths inside Control Module 1 and Control Module 2 between their respective input and output series terminals to confirm that, when switched ON, each module actually provides a low‑resistance connection (≈0 Ω) in the forward direction and is not internally wired to bypass or short the supply.
